verses.verse: For the Chief Musician. A Psalm. A Song of David. Praise <WH8416> waiteth <WH1747> for thee <WH430>, O God, in Zion <WH6726>; And unto thee shall the vow <WH5088> be performed <WH7999>.
O thou that hearest <WH8085> prayer <WH8605>, Unto thee shall all flesh <WH1320> come <WH935>.
Iniquities <WH1697> prevail <WH1396> against me <WH6588>: As for our transgressions, thou wilt forgive them <WH3722>.

Blessed <WH835> is the man whom thou choosest <WH977>, and causest to approach <WH7126> unto thee <WH7931>, That he may dwell in thy courts <WH2691>: We shall be satisfied <WH7646> with the goodness <WH2898> of thy house <WH1004>, Thy holy <WH6918> temple <WH1964>.

By terrible things <WH3372> thou wilt answer <WH6030> us in righteousness <WH6664>, Oh God <WH430> of our salvation <WH3468>, Thou that art the confidence <WH4009> of all the ends <WH7099> of the earth <WH776>, And of them that are afar off <WH7350> upon the sea <WH3220>:
Who by his strength <WH3581> setteth fast <WH3559> the mountains <WH2022>, Being girded <WH247> about with might <WH1369>;
Who stilleth <WH7623> the roaring <WH7588> of the seas <WH3220>, The roaring <WH7588> of their waves <WH1530>, And the tumult <WH1995> of the peoples <WH3816>.

They also that dwell <WH3427> in the uttermost parts <WH7099> are afraid <WH3372> at thy tokens <WH226>: Thou makest the outgoings <WH4161> of the morning <WH1242> and evening <WH6153> to rejoice <WH7442>.

Thou visitest <WH6485> the earth <WH776>, and waterest <WH7783> it <WH7227>, Thou greatly enrichest <WH6238> it <WH6388>; The river of God <WH430> is full <WH4390> of water <WH4325>: Thou providest <WH3559> them grain <WH1715>, when thou hast so prepared the earth <WH3559>.

Thou waterest <WH7301> its furrows <WH1417> abundantly <WH7301>; Thou settlest <WH5181> the ridges <WH8525> thereof <WH4127>: Thou makest it soft with showers <WH7241>; Thou blessest <WH1288> the springing thereof <WH6780>.
Thou crownest <WH5849> the year <WH8141> with thy goodness <WH2896>; And thy paths <WH4570> drop <WH7491> fatness <WH1880>.
They drop <WH7491> upon the pastures <WH4999> of the wilderness <WH4057>; And the hills <WH1389> are girded <WH2296> with joy <WH1524>.
The pastures <WH3733> are clothed <WH3847> with flocks <WH6629>; The valleys <WH6010> also are covered over <WH5848> with grain <WH1250>; They shout for joy <WH7321>, they also sing <WH7891>.
